				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\lambda $$\end{document}λ, drive and sustain the infection process through a contact web disentangled into two aspects: mobility as movement trends and proximity as proxy for interpersonal distance. This framework takes into account a natural delay between time of contacts and the triggering of new infection chains, making the model a forward estimate for the values of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_t$$\end{document}Rt to come. This perspective can provide useful insight for policy makers and regulators planning mobility restrictions or other strategies for mitigating the diffusion of an epidemic like CoViD-19.

